    • Constructor Detail

      • MetroTrack

        public MetroTrack(Metro metro,
                  java.lang.Object name,
                  java.util.Collection<java.lang.Object> tags,
                  MetroSequence sequence)
        Create a MetroTrack object with default synchronizing status. This constructor is public but this is usually called only from Metro#createTrack(String, Collection, MetroSequence, MetroSyncType, MetroTrack, double) and users should not call this constructor directory. Though it is still left public for further hacking.
        Parameters:
        metro - Specifying the parent metro object.
        name - Specifying the identifier of the track.
        tags - Specifying the tag strings. This could be null and treated as an empty set.
        sequence - Specifying the sequence object to play.
